SCHEMA: validation/validation_result.schema
schema_id: dominium.schema.validation.validation_result
schema_version: 1.0.0
stability: core

PURPOSE:
- Define the canonical structured result payload for unified validation suites and aggregate `validate --all` runs.

NON-SEMANTICS:
- Validation results report governance state and do not mutate TruthModel.
- Validation suite ordering is deterministic and registry-driven.

REQUIRED SHAPE:
record validation_result
  required:
    - schema_version: semver
    - validation_id: id
    - suite_id: id
    - category_id: id
    - profile: enum(FAST|STRICT|FULL)
    - result: enum(complete|refused|skipped)
    - message: string
    - suite_order: u32
    - adapter_id: id
    - description: string
    - checked_paths: list<string>
    - errors: list<finding>
    - warnings: list<finding>
    - metrics: map
    - fingerprints: map
    - legacy_adapters: list<adapter_row>
    - suite_results: list<validation_result>
    - deterministic_fingerprint: sha256
    - extensions: map

INVARIANTS:
- suite ordering MUST follow `validation_suite_registry.json`
- `deterministic_fingerprint` MUST be computed with the fingerprint field blanked
- aggregate `validate --all` reports MUST use `suite_id = validate.all`
- legacy adapters are reporting metadata only and do not authorize parallel validation semantics
